<div class="container">
  <h1>Navigating the Internet Safely</h1>
  <div class="content">
    <div class="text-container">
      <p>Welcome to the next lesson! In this lesson, we will cover how to navigate the internet safely. The internet can be a powerful tool for finding information, staying connected, and learning new things, but it is important to stay safe while using it.</p>

      <p>When browsing the internet, itâ€™s important to use a <strong>secure browser</strong> like Chrome, Firefox, or Edge. These browsers help protect your information and alert you to potentially unsafe websites.</p>

      <p>A key part of safe internet browsing is recognizing <strong>secure websites</strong>. Secure websites will have an address that starts with <strong>"https://"</strong>, where the "s" stands for secure. You should also see a small padlock icon next to the web address, which indicates that your connection is private.</p>

      <p>Be cautious about the information you share online. You should never share personal details such as your <strong>address, phone number, passwords, or financial information</strong> unless you are sure the website is trustworthy and secure.</p>

      <p>Avoid clicking on suspicious links or opening unexpected attachments, especially in emails. This is a common way for malicious software, called <strong>malware</strong>, to infect your computer. Always verify the source before clicking a link or downloading anything.</p>

      <p>Using <strong>strong passwords</strong> for your online accounts is also a key aspect of internet safety. Never use the same password for multiple accounts, and consider using a password manager to keep track of them.</p>

      <p>Another way to stay safe is to keep your <strong>antivirus software</strong> up to date. Antivirus software helps protect your computer from malware and other security threats while you are browsing online.</p>

      <p>Lastly, be cautious when using <strong>public Wi-Fi</strong>. Public networks can be less secure, making it easier for hackers to access your information. Avoid accessing sensitive accounts or making online purchases while connected to public Wi-Fi.</p>

      <!-- Add multiple-choice quiz here -->
