        <p>1. What should you look for to ensure a website is secure?</p>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">The address starts with "https" and there is a padlock icon</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">The address starts with "http"</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">It has many images</button>

        <p>2. What should you avoid sharing online?</p>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">Your address, phone number, and financial information</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">Your favorite color</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">A picture of your pet</button>

        <p>3. Why should you be careful when using public Wi-Fi?</p>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">Public Wi-Fi can be insecure and make it easier for hackers to access your information</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">Public Wi-Fi always requires a password</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">Public Wi-Fi is too slow</button>
      </div>

      <p>Great job completing this lesson on navigating the internet safely! Feel free to go back to the main modules or move on to the next lesson.</p>
